On July 15, 2010, Earl Dolive, a member of the Board of Directors of Aaron's, Inc (the "Company"), provided the Chairman of the Board with written notice of his resignation, effective as of July 15, 2010. Prior to his resignation, Mr. Dolive served on the Board's Audit Committee.
In light of Mr. Dolive's 33 years of dedicated and distinguished Board service and valuable contributions to the growth and development of the Company, Mr. Dolive will serve as Director Emeritus upon his resignation.
 
Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned hereunto duly authorized.

